hopobject.body: Nice to meet you acheter temovate Thanks to this largesse, Tehran now holds sway over Assad’s decisions. He has become a leader kept in power by foreign bayonets, against the furious opposition of many of his people. In all probability, therefore, Iran is now using Syria as a theatre for testing America’s resolve. In particular, it will be watching to see if Assad can get away with jumping over Mr Obama’s red line when it comes to using chemical weapons. If that happens – if Assad can gas hundreds of his enemies and pay no price – then the strength of America’s other red line in the Middle East, the one that presently constrains Iran’s nuclear ambitions, would be called into question.
